"Abstract In a recent case (Switzerland Insurance Australia v Dundean Distributors Pty Ltd), the Victorian Court of Appeal had to decide precisely what kind of damage is likely to be covered where computer equipment is ensured. A leading Australian law firm, Phillips Fox, says that the issue is whether damage to computer software and damage to the integrity of data on a hard disk fell under the policy, which insured Dundean's electronic equipment against accidental loss or damage. Consequential loss was limited to specific and unrelated provisions."
